summary: I know y'all must be so tired of seeing me sharing all my thoughts, and I'm sorry for that but I can't help it. So, I'm gonna...
body:
I know y'all must be so tired of seeing me sharing all my thoughts, and I’m sorry for that but I can’t help it. So, I’m gonna say something that really makes me think a lot.

It’s so interesting how Eve feels comfortable to say to Villanelle everything she wants to say, even knowing her so recently. In ep 5, even knowing Villanelle could kill her using just her hands, she was bold enough to call Villanelle an asshole, she was bold enough to try to stab her, she was bold enough to say “i’m gonna find the thing you care about, and I’m gonna kill it“, she was bold enough to destroy Villanelle’s apartment in ep 8 and say all those things. She feels comfortable to be herself when she is with Villanelle, even knowing Villanelle is a psycho.

But with Niko, she’s always so careful with what she will say, with what she will do. Even being married to him for 10 (?) years, she doesn’t feel she can be herself with him. Shes always asking “are you annoyed?” or “why are you so angry?”. She hides the puncture she did in her leg with a knife from him. She apologizes when she shows her interest for murder to him. She just says or does what she wants to say or do in his presence when she is angry, but when she’s “normal” - or trying to be normal - she is so controlled, so policed. Like she knew he is not ready to know who she really is. And it is really interesting to me.
